15/09/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH and Greece sealed an agreement Wednesday (14 September) on military co-operation in 2006.
The programme provides for continued Greek support of the BiH Armed Forces and the training of BiH soldiers at Greek military academies.
BiH also signed agreements Wednesday with Macedonia;
these deal with legal assistance concerning civil and criminal issues, as well as property settlements.
(Fena, Macedonian Government Web site - 14/09/05)
